It's been a week since President Trump shut the government down. Until he understands that the right choice is the American people and not the ineffective border wall, it does not appear this #TrumpShutdown will end. https://www.nbcdfw.com/news/politics/House-lawmakers-on-Partial-Govt-Shutdown-503575171.html …

And let us also keep the 420,000 federal employees who are working during the holidays without pay because of the #TrumpShutdown in our thoughts. We are grateful that they are fulfilling their responsibilities to our country even when the president is not.

As we rejoice and spend time with our loved ones, let us offer our prayers for the 14,000 unaccompanied, immigrant children who are still separated from their families and living without knowing when they will be reunited with their parents.
Wishing everyone celebrating a very Merry Christmas! May this day bring peace and joy! pic.twitter.com/hZvUCTYF5I
Here's my full statement on the #TrumpShutdown: https://ebjohnson.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/congresswoman-johnson-s-statement-on-the-government-shutdown …

Democrats presented Pres. Trump with a simple proposal days ago: keep the government funded through a bipartisan plan that provided more than $1 billion for border security. Pres. Trump instead chose an unattainable, irresponsible $5 billion wall over the American people.

House Democrats and Senators from both parties are ready to keep the government open. The Senate has already voted to do so. If the government does indeed shutdown it will be because POTUS rejected a bipartisan deal. #TrumpShutdown
